    • Method Detail

      • open

        public void open()
          throws IOException,
                 InterruptedException,
                 ExecutionException
        Opens the AmqpsIotHubConnection creating a new AmqpsIotHubConnectionBaseHandler.

        If the current AmqpsIotHubConnection.ReactorState is not OPEN, this method will create a new IotHubSasToken and use it to create a new AmqpsIotHubConnectionBaseHandler. This method will start the Reactor, set the current AmqpsIotHubConnection.ReactorState to OPEN, and open the AmqpsIotHubConnection for sending.

        Throws:
        IOException - if the AmqpsIotHubConnectionBaseHandler has not been initialized.
        InterruptedException - if there is a problem acquiring the semaphore for the Reactor.
        ExecutionException - If the CompletableFuture in reactorReady() completed exceptionally

      • close

        public void close()
        Closes the AmqpsIotHubConnection and invalidates the Reactor object.

        If the current AmqpsIotHubConnection.ReactorState is not CLOSED, this function will invalidate the current Reactor object, set the current AmqpsIotHubConnection.ReactorState to CLOSED, and free the current AmqpsIotHubConnectionBaseHandler.

        public void sendMessageResult(IotHubMessageResult result)

        Sends the message result for the previously received message.

      • send

        protected void send()
             throws IOException
        Attempts to asynchronously send the message at the head of the queue. It is strongly recommend to synchronize calls to this method. This AmqpsIotHubConnection handles all calls to this method.

        Only the first call to this method will result in an attempt to send. Until the message has been sent and acknowledged by the receiver, all other calls to this method will do nothing. Once a message has been sent and acknowledged by the receiver, this method is called again. If a message has been passed down to the handler for sending but the message isn't sent after a default constant number of seconds, the AmqpsTransport will set an ERROR status code on the message and it will placed back onto the queue.

        Throws:
        IOException - If AmqpsIotHubConnectionBaseHandler has not been initialized.

      • lockSending

        protected void lockSending()
        "Locks" sending by setting a flag to false. Causes invocations of send() to do nothing.

      • openSending

        protected void openSending()
        "Unlocks" sending by setting a flag to true. Allows invocations of send() to proceed normally. Invokes the send() method.

      • getCompletionStatus

        protected boolean getCompletionStatus()
                               throws ExecutionException,
                                      InterruptedException
        Every AmqpsIotHubConnection has a CompletableFuture completionStatus variable. This can be used by the AmqpsTransport to know when/if the AmqpsIotHubConnection has completed work successfully or not.

        The completionStatus variable is completed whenever the AmqpsIotHubConnection has exhausted the current message queue successfully or whenever there is an error sending a message.

        Returns:
        The boolean value of the completion status.
        Throws:
        ExecutionException - If this future completed exceptionally
        InterruptedException - If the current thread was interrupted
